post_text:
Jesus Figueroa is an 8th grade graduate of the Future Investment Middle School class of 2020. He has shown high academic achievement at every level of his education while at the Griffin Foundation schools.

This coming school year 2020-2021, he will be attending University High. We wish him well in his new endeavors and know that there are no limits on what he can achieve. To his parents, great job!

To our graduates of the 2020 class, please remember the FIMS Motto and continue to follow your dreams; never stop believing in yourself.

We are now accepting students enrollment applications for the upcoming 20-21 school year.

From:
The GFSD family and Mr. Griffin

post_text: The Griffin Foundation School District had their end of school year drive through parade. Students, parents, teachers, and staff had a great time celebrating this special event; we look forward to educating and working with our students next school year. We are accepting student enrollment packets for the 20-21 upcoming school year, call for more information. Most importantly, I wish to thank our teachers for the wonderful job they did working with their students online and providing mail out work packets. post_text: Attention Parents we are having a book fair at our school. The event will be going on till February 8th. The shopping times will be from 7:30am to 8:30am and from 3pm to 4pm but not on Wednesday. Wednesday shopping time in the evening will be from 1pm to 2pm. Please support our school by purchasing books from our book fair. Our goal is 250+ books that must be sold. If you have any questions please give our school a call.
